                n n        Civic Engagement n       Expand Civic Engagement menu  n n                  Registration n                  n n                  Education n                  n n                  Participation n                 Eyebrow menu Donate UIC Connection Student Affairs UIC menu UIC edu Campus Map Ignite  Exploring Leaders Program  Participant Application Deadline  n nShare this on Facebook n n n n n n Share this on Facebook  n n        January          n n     n Ignite is an eight week program that supports first  and second year undergraduate students as they begin to navigate and explore the concepts of leadership and self reflection  Meeting once a week with peer facilitators and mentors  Ignite participants gain access to valuable campus resources  along with gaining insight into the values  support  and competencies needed for positive involvement at UIC  Using a passion driven action plan  students distinguish key identities  values  and issues that matter to them  Upon completion of the program  students will feel better connected with the UIC community  feel more in touch with their personal goals  and become a change agent for the future Participant Application  Due January          at      pm uic edu IgniteLeadership go uic edu IgniteLeadership Contact slce uic edu Date posted Nov          Date updated Nov           n nUIC Logo n n n n UIC Logo  n          Student Leadership and Civic Engagement n         Quick Links Donate Events Tools Log Hours Newsletter Sign Up Resources Register To Vote UIC Connection Button Menu Leadership Service Civic Engagement Contact               slce uic edu Social Media Accounts  nFacebook n Facebook  nTwitter n Twitter  nInstagram n Instagram  nYouTube n YouTube UIC edu links UIC edu Academic Calendar Athletics Campus Directory Disability Resources Emergency Information Event Calendar Job Openings Library Maps UIC Today UI Health Veterans Affairs Privacy Statement Campuses University of Illinois System Urb